result.execSummary:
The defendant Alysia M Coronado was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Theft-Movable Property fr. Person/Corpse [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all prison wages at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substance without a valid prescription and then take medications as prescribed.

Defendant shall notify the agent of any change in prescription or new prescription within 48 hours of the change.

Defendant shall have no contact with Tanya Kuells, Jimmie Castro, Sr., Sara Brushwood or Nathan Meleski.

Defendant shall not be present in any bars, traverns or establishment where primary purpose is the sale/service/consumption of alcohol.  

Defendant shall not possess any drug paraphernalia.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent and comply with treatment recommendations.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample, unless previously provided.  

Defendant shall submit to random drug screens.

Defendant shall pay any supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and comply with recommendations.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or schooling or combination of both to equal full time.
